# SPARQL Navigator

A plain JavaScript library for navigating SKOS ontologies via SPARQL endpoints.

## Structure

- `sparql-navigator.js` - Core navigator library (reusable)
- `navigator.css` - Shared styles
- `his-central/` - HIS-Central navigator instance
- `whos/` - WHOS navigator instance

## Usage

Each navigator instance (his-central, whos) loads its own `config.json` file containing:
- `endpoint`: SPARQL endpoint URL
- `title`: Display title

The navigator automatically:
- Fetches top concepts from the SPARQL endpoint
- Displays them in an expandable tree structure
- Supports language filtering
- Sends messages to parent window when clicking concept URIs

## Adding a New Navigator Instance

1. Create a new directory (e.g., `new-navigator/`)
2. Copy `index.html` from an existing navigator
3. Create a `config.json` with your endpoint and title
4. Update the HTML title and meta description

## Development

The library is plain JavaScript with no build step required. Simply edit the files and refresh the browser.
